{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_1","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,240p' __issue_context__.json\"","aggregated_output":"{\n  \"body\": \"Following up on comments in https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29539.\\n\\nThere are currently 5 nested GO terms for Entner-Doudoroff pathways, though only 1 has ever been used in annotation:\\n\\n```\\nEntner-Doudoroff pathway [0 direct annotations]\\n    |_Entner-Doudoroff pathway through 6-phosphogluconate (MetaCyc:PWY-8004) [4 EXP annotations + InterPro:IPR004786]*\\n    |_Entner-Doudoroff pathway through gluconate [0 direct annotations]\\n        |_Entner-Doudoroff pathway through gluconate to D-glyceraldehyde (MetaCyc:NPGLUCAT-PWY) [0 annotations]\\n        |_Entner-Doudoroff pathway through gluconate to D-glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate (MetaCyc:PWY-2221) [0 annotations]\\n```\\n\\n* The 4 EXP annotations are to Thermoplasma Ta0809, Picrophilus PTO0332, and E.coli Eda by UniProt/EcoCyc\\n\\n\\nAs suggested in https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29539, the 4 child terms should be merged into the parent \\\"Entner-Doudoroff pathway\\\" (GO:0061678), consistent with MetaCyc classing these as 'variant pathways' and the fact that such variants are better represented as GO-CAMs. Morever, the MetaCyc descriptions of the variants differ slightly (in their start/end points) from the GO descriptions.\\n\\nThe individual MetaCyc IDs should be made narrowMatch xrefs on the parent term GO:0061678.\\nAlso add a fourth variant, MetaCyc:ENTNER-DOUDOROFF-PWY, as narrowMatch xref.\\nAnd remove the 'MetaCyc:Entner-Doudoroff-Pathways' xref since that is the grouping class.\\n\\nIndividual GO term entries are shown below:\\n\\nid: GO:0061678\\nname: Entner-Doudoroff pathway\\nnamespace: biological_process\\ndef: \\\"A cellular carbohydrate catabolic process that converts a carbohydrate to pyruvate and either glyceraldehyde or glyceraldehyde-3 phosphate by dehydration and aldol cleavage via a gluconate or 6-phosphogluconate intermediate.\\\" [GOC:dph, PMID:12921536]\\nxref: MetaCyc:Entner-Doudoroff-Pathways\\nis_a: GO:0016052 ! carbohydrate catabolic process\\nrelationship: has_primary_output CHEBI:15361 ! pyruvate\\ncreated_by: dph\\ncreation_date: 2015-01-16T15:28:25Z\\n\\n\\nid: GO:0009255\\nname: Entner-Doudoroff pathway through 6-phosphogluconate\\nnamespace: biological_process\\ndef: \\\"A pathway that converts a carbohydrate to pyruvate and glyceraldehyde-3 phosphate by producing 6-phosphogluconate and then dehydrating it.\\\" [GOC:jl, MetaCyc:PWY-8004, PMID:12921356, PMID:12981024]\\nxref: MetaCyc:PWY-8004\\nis_a: GO:0005975 ! carbohydrate metabolic process\\nis_a: GO:0044281 ! small molecule metabolic process\\nis_a: GO:0061678 ! Entner-Doudoroff pathway\\nintersection_of: GO:0061678 ! Entner-Doudoroff pathway\\nintersection_of: ends_with GO:0008675 ! 2-dehydro-3-deoxy-phosphogluconate aldolase activity\\nintersection_of: has_intermediate CHEBI:58759 ! 6-phosphonatooxy-D-gluconate\\nintersection_of: has_part GO:0004456 ! phosphogluconate dehydratase activity\\nintersection_of: has_primary_output CHEBI:15361 ! pyruvate\\nintersection_of: has_primary_output CHEBI:58027 ! glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate(2-)\\n\\n\\nid: GO:0061679\\nname: Entner-Doudoroff pathway through gluconate\\nnamespace: biological_process\\ndef: \\\"The Entner-Doudoroff pathway that proceeds through a D-gluconate intermediate.\\\" [GOC:dph, PMID:12921536]\\nsynonym: \\\"gluconate pathway\\\" RELATED []\\nis_a: GO:0061678 ! Entner-Doudoroff pathway\\nintersection_of: GO:0061678 ! Entner-Doudoroff pathway\\nintersection_of: has_intermediate CHEBI:18391 ! D-gluconate\\nintersection_of: has_part GO:0047929 ! gluconate dehydratase activity\\nintersection_of: has_part GO:0047935 ! glucose 1-dehydrogenase (NADP+) activity\\nintersection_of: has_primary_output CHEBI:15361 ! pyruvate\\ncreated_by: dph\\ncreation_date: 2015-01-16T15:41:22Z\\n\\n\\nid: GO:0061680\\nname: Entner-Doudoroff pathway through gluconate to D-glyceraldehyde\\nnamespace: biological_process\\ndef: \\\"The Entner-Doudoroff pathway that proceeds through a D-gluconate intermediate and yields pyruvate and D-glyceraldehyde.\\\" [GOC:dph, MetaCyc:NPGLUCAT-PWY, PMID:12921536]\\nxref: MetaCyc:NPGLUCAT-PWY\\nis_a: GO:0019595 ! non-phosphorylated glucose catabolic process\\nis_a: GO:0061679 ! Entner-Doudoroff pathway through gluconate\\nintersection_of: GO:0061679 ! Entner-Doudoroff pathway through gluconate\\nintersection_of: ends_with GO:0061677 ! 2-dehydro-3-deoxy-D-gluconate aldolase activity\\nintersection_of: has_primary_output CHEBI:17378 ! D-glyceraldehyde\\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \\\"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28392\\\" xsd:anyURI\\ncreated_by: dph\\ncreation_date: 2015-01-22T08:51:31Z\\n\\n\\nid: GO:0061681\\nname: Entner-Doudoroff pathway through gluconate to D-glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate\\nnamespace: biological_process\\ndef: \\\"The Entner-Doudoroff pathway that proceeds through a D-gluconate intermediate and yields pyruvate and D-glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate.\\\" [GOC:dph, PMID:12921536]\\nxref: MetaCyc:PWY-2221\\nis_a: GO:0061679 ! Entner-Doudoroff pathway through gluconate\\nintersection_of: GO:0061679 ! Entner-Doudoroff pathway through gluconate\\nintersection_of: ends_with GO:0008675 ! 2-dehydro-3-deoxy-phosphogluconate aldolase activity\\nintersection_of: has_part GO:0008673 ! 2-dehydro-3-deoxygluconokinase activity\\nintersection_of: has_primary_output CHEBI:58027 ! glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate(2-)\\ncreated_by: dph\\ncreation_date: 2015-01-22T08:55:22Z\\n\\n\\n\",\n  \"comments\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws8AAAABAykORg\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"raymond91125\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"Also there is GO:0061688 glycolytic process via Entner-Doudoroff Pathway, 10 IEA annotations, no EXP. @sjm41 I think this too should be 'merged' into (obsolete with consider) GO:0061678 Entner-Doudoroff pathway or GO:0006096 glycolytic process. Do you agree?\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-29T22:28:31Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31916#issuecomment-4347989574\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws8AAAABA2aYBQ\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"sjm41\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"> Also there is GO:0061688 glycolytic process via Entner-Doudoroff Pathway, 10 IEA annotations, no EXP. @sjm41 I think this too should be 'merged' into (obsolete with consider) GO:0061678 Entner-Doudoroff pathway or GO:0006096 glycolytic process. Do you agree?\\n\\n@raymond91125  Yes, I'd suggest that term is merged into its parent GO:0006096 glycolytic process. Thanks.\\n\\nI'll note that the 10 IEA annotations are all by CGD, based on evidence from [PomBase:SPAC4G9.12](https://www.pombase.org/gene/SPAC4G9.12) or [PomBase:SPBC660.16](https://www.pombase.org/gene/SPBC660.16).\\nLooking at those records in PomBase, they are annotated with a different BP \\\"pentose-phosphate shunt, oxidative branch (GO:0009051)\\\". So CGD may want to change those annotations anyway. (I don't know who the CGD contact is.)\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-30T11:23:04Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31916#issuecomment-4352022533\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws8AAAABA2pKsQ\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"pgaudet\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"CGD contact is @jlewsmith \\n\\nI assume that the IEA will get update automatically ? \",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-30T12:01:10Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31916#issuecomment-4352264881\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws8AAAABA2ruNQ\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"sjm41\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"> I assume that the IEA will get update automatically ?\\n\\nThat's what I thought, so I was surprised to see the mismatch between the current PomBase BP and the CGD annotations!\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-30T12:07:34Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31916#issuecomment-4352306741\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws8AAAABA2tkbA\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"pgaudet\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"I don't know how frequent CGD releases are.\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-30T12:12:36Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [\n        {\n          \"content\": \"THUMBS_UP\",\n          \"users\": {\n            \"totalCount\": 1\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31916#issuecomment-4352337004\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws8AAAABBKv3NQ\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"raymond91125\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"@dragon-ai-agent please obsolete with replaced_by:\\nGO:0009255 Entner-Doudoroff pathway through 6-phosphogluconate -> GO:0061678 Entner-Doudoroff pathway\\nGO:0061679 Entner-Doudoroff pathway through gluconate -> GO:0061678 Entner-Doudoroff pathway\\nGO:0061680 Entner-Doudoroff pathway through gluconate to D-glyceraldehyde -> GO:0061678 Entner-Doudoroff pathway\\nGO:0061681 Entner-Doudoroff pathway through gluconate to D-glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate -> GO:0061678 Entner-Doudoroff pathway\\nGO:0061688 glycolytic process via Entner-Doudoroff Pathway -> GO:0006096 glycolytic process\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2026-05-04T18:11:37Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [\n        {\n          \"content\": \"EYES\",\n          \"users\": {\n            \"totalCount\": 1\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31916#issuecomment-4373346101\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws8AAAABBKwB_g\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"dragon-ai-agent\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"🤖 Working on it...\\n\\nFollow along: [View workflow run](https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/actions/runs/25335280243)\\n\\n*— @dragon-ai-agent*\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2026-05-04T18:11:59Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31916#issuecomment-4373348862\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": true\n    }\n  ],\n  \"title\": \"Review of Entner-Doudoroff pathways\",\n  \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31916\"\n}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
