{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_49","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"rg -n -U 'name: obsolete .*\\\\n(?:.*\\\\n){0,8}.*term_tracker_item.*\\\\n(?:.*\\\\n){0,8}.*term_tracker_item' src/ontology/go-edit.obo | sed -n '1,80p'\"","aggregated_output":"5324:name: obsolete nucleotide-excision repair, DNA duplex unwinding\n5325:namespace: biological_process\n5326:def: \"OBSOLETE. The unwinding, or local denaturation, of the DNA duplex to create a bubble around the site of the DNA damage.\" [GOC:elh, PMID:10197977]\n5327:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that the term represents a molecular function.\n5328:property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29153\" xsd:anyURI\n5329:is_obsolete: true\n5330:\n5331:[Term]\n5332:id: GO:0000718\n5333:name: obsolete nucleotide-excision repair, DNA damage removal\n5334:namespace: biological_process\n5335:def: \"OBSOLETE. The removal of the oligonucleotide that contains the DNA damage. The oligonucleotide is formed by dual incisions that flank the site of DNA damage.\" [GOC:elh, PMID:10197977]\n5336:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term represents a molecular function.\n5337:property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29220\" xsd:anyURI\n5592:name: obsolete karyogamy involved in conjugation with mutual genetic exchange\n5593:namespace: biological_process\n5594:def: \"OBSOLETE. During sexual reproduction, the creation of a single nucleus from two nuclei as a result of fusing the nuclear envelopes that surround each nuclei. This takes place following the mutual exchange of one of the two nuclei produced by the mitosis that follows the second meiotic nuclear division. This occurs in ciliated protozoans such as Tetrahymena.\" [GOC:mah, GOC:pg]\n5595:comment: This term was obsoleted because it is a pre-composed term that should be captured as a GO-CAM model.\n5596:synonym: \"karyogamy involved in conjugation without cellular fusion\" EXACT [GOC:dph, GOC:tb]\n5597:property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/16248\" xsd:anyURI\n5598:property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31306\" xsd:anyURI\n5834:name: obsolete negative adaptation of signaling pathway by response to pheromone involved in pheromone-induced unidirectional conjugation\n5835:namespace: biological_process\n5836:def: \"OBSOLETE. In organisms that undergo pheromone-induced unidirectional conjugation, the process involved in desensitization following exposure to pheromone stimulus that acts to down-regulate further stimulation or block initial conjugation responses.\" [GOC:clt]\n5837:comment: This term was obsoleted because it is a pre-composed term that should be captured as a GO-CAM model.\n5838:synonym: \"adaptation to pheromone during pheromone-induced unidirectional conjugation\" RELATED [GOC:dph, GOC:tb]\n5839:synonym: \"desensitization to pheromone during pheromone-induced unidirectional conjugation\" EXACT []\n5840:synonym: \"negative adaptation of signalling pathway by response to pheromone involved in pheromone-induced unidirectional conjugation\" EXACT [GOC:mah]\n5841:property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31254\" xsd:anyURI\n5842:is_obsolete: true\n5843:\n5844:[Term]\n5845:id: GO:0000767\n5846:name: obsolete cell morphogenesis involved in conjugation\n5847:namespace: biological_process\n5848:def: \"OBSOLETE. The change in form (cell shape and size) that occurs during sexual reproduction in order to facilitate direct contact between the compatible mating types.\" [GOC:elh]\n5849:comment: This term was obsoleted because it is an unnecessary grouping class.\n5850:property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/22916\" xsd:anyURI\n6997:name: obsolete amino acid catabolic process to alcohol via Ehrlich pathway\n6998:namespace: biological_process\n6999:def: \"OBSOLETE. The chemical reactions and pathways involving the catabolism of amino acids to produce alcohols with one carbon less than the starting amino acid. In S. cerevisiae, this is known to occur for leucine, isoleucine, valine, methionine, phenylalanine, tyrosine, or tryptophan. Often referred to as the Ehrlich pathway, these reactions generally occur during fermentation to produce a variety of alcohols, often collectively referred to as fusel alcohols. Depending on the redox state of the cells, carboxylic acid derivatives may be produced instead of alcohols.\" [GOC:krc, PMID:18281432]\n7000:comment: This term was obsoleted because it represents multiple specific pathways. Consider specific amino acid catabolic processes.\n7001:property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31839\" xsd:anyURI\n7002:is_obsolete: true\n7003:\n7004:[Term]\n7005:id: GO:0000948\n7006:name: obsolete amino acid catabolic process to carboxylic acid via Ehrlich pathway\n7007:namespace: biological_process\n7008:def: \"OBSOLETE. The chemical reactions and pathways involving the catabolism of amino acids to produce carboxylic acids with one carbon less than the starting amino acid. In S. cerevisiae, this is known to occur for leucine, isoleucine, valine, methionine, phenylalanine, tyrosine, or tryptophan. Often referred to as the Ehrlich pathway, these reactions generally occur during fermentation to produce a variety of carboxylic acids, sometimes collectively referred to as fusel acids. Depending on the redox state of the cells, alcohol derivatives may be produced instead of carboxylic acids.\" [GOC:krc, PMID:18281432]\n7009:comment: This term was obsoleted because it represents multiple specific pathways. Consider specific amino acid catabolic processes.\n7010:property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31839\" xsd:anyURI\n7879:name: obsolete RNA polymerase I activity\n7880:namespace: molecular_function\n7881:def: \"OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: nucleoside triphosphate + RNA(n) = diphosphate + RNA(n+1). Utilizes a DNA template that contains an RNA polymerase I specific promoter to direct initiation and catalyzes DNA-template-directed extension of the 3'-end of an RNA strand by one nucleotide at a time. Can initiate a chain 'de novo'.\" [GOC:txnOH]\n7882:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term is equivalent to DNA-directed 5'-3' RNA polymerase activity.\n7883:synonym: \"DNA-directed RNA polymerase activity involved in transcription from RNA polymerase I promoter\" EXACT []\n7884:property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/23779\" xsd:anyURI\n7885:property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28520\" xsd:anyURI\n7893:name: obsolete RNA polymerase II activity\n7894:namespace: molecular_function\n7895:def: \"OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: nucleoside triphosphate + RNA(n) = diphosphate + RNA(n+1). Utilizes a DNA template that contains an RNA polymerase II specific promoter to direct initiation and catalyses DNA-template-directed extension of the 3'-end of an RNA strand by one nucleotide at a time. Can initiate a chain 'de novo'.\" [GOC:txnOH]\n7896:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term is equivalent to DNA-directed 5'-3' RNA polymerase activity.\n7897:synonym: \"DNA-directed RNA polymerase activity involved in transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter\" EXACT []\n7898:property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/23779\" xsd:anyURI\n7899:property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28520\" xsd:anyURI\n7907:name: obsolete RNA polymerase III activity\n7908:namespace: molecular_function\n7909:def: \"OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: nucleoside triphosphate + RNA(n) = diphosphate + RNA(n+1). Utilizes a DNA template that contains an RNA polymerase III specific promoter to direct initiation and catalyses DNA-template-directed extension of the 3'-end of an RNA strand by one nucleotide at a time. Can initiate a chain 'de novo'.\" [GOC:txnOH]\n7910:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term is equivalent to DNA-directed 5'-3' RNA polymerase activity.\n7911:synonym: \"DNA-directed RNA polymerase activity involved in transcription from RNA polymerase III promoter\" EXACT []\n7912:property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/23779\" xsd:anyURI\n7913:property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28520\" xsd:anyURI\n7921:name: obsolete RNA polymerase IV activity\n7922:namespace: molecular_function\n7923:def: \"OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: nucleoside triphosphate + RNA(n) = diphosphate + RNA(n+1). Utilizes a DNA template that contains an RNA polymerase IV specific promoter to direct initiation and catalyses DNA-template-directed extension of the 3'-end of an RNA strand by one nucleotide at a time. Can initiate a chain 'de novo'.\" [GOC:txnOH]\n7924:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term is equivalent to DNA-directed 5'-3' RNA polymerase activity.\n7925:synonym: \"DNA-directed RNA polymerase activity involved in transcription from RNA polymerase IV promoter\" EXACT []\n7926:property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/23779\" xsd:anyURI\n7927:property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28520\" xsd:anyURI\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
